        <!-- Chapter 2: The Squad -->
        <section id="squad" class="content-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="chapter-header">
                    <span class="chapter-number">Chapter 2</span>
                    <h2>The Squad</h2>
                    <p class="chapter-subtitle">Team roles and formations for sprint success</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="squad-overview">
                    <div class="squad-guidelines">
                        <h4>Team Formation Guidelines</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Core Team Size:</strong> 5-7 contributors for optimal decision-making</li>
                            <li><strong>Decision Authority:</strong> Clear Decider role prevents analysis paralysis</li>
                            <li><strong>Specialist Integration:</strong> Bring in experts for specific phases as needed</li>
                            <li><strong>Cross-functional Balance:</strong> Technical, business, and user perspectives represented</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="squad-grid">
                    <div class="role-card facilitator">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Facilitator</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Head Coach</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Runs the room, protects time, keeps energy and decisions flowing</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Process enforcement and time management</li>
                                <li>Energy management and group dynamics</li>
                                <li>Decision facilitation and conflict resolution</li>
                                <li>Exercise instruction and quality control</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Present for all sprint activities. Critical for maintaining momentum and ensuring proper execution of methodologies.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card decider">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Decider</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Team Captain</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Ultimate decision-maker when votes are split, often founder or key executive</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Final decisions on direction and priorities</li>
                                <li>Vision alignment and strategic direction</li>
                                <li>Resource allocation and timeline approval</li>
                                <li>Stakeholder communication and buy-in</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Present for key decision points (Supervote, Go/No-Go decisions). Must be available for rapid consultation during sprint.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card architect">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Solution Architect (AI)</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Offensive Coordinator</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Translates business goals into working backlog, technical feasibility audits</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Technical feasibility assessment and architecture planning</li>
                                <li>AI integration strategy and opportunity identification</li>
                                <li>Compliance mapping and constraint analysis</li>
                                <li>Data flow and integration planning</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Critical during Understand and Prototype phases. Leads technical feasibility discussions in MVP sprints.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card developer">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Lead Developer</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Star Player</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Builds and tests features, ensures technical feasibility, prototyping</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Feature development and technical validation</li>
                                <li>Prototype building with AI tooling (v0.dev/Replit)</li>
                                <li>Code quality assurance and testing</li>
                                <li>Technical constraint identification</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Essential for Prototype phase and all MVP development phases. Provides technical input during Understand phase.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card pm">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Project Manager</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Team Manager</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">When/how-much/risk guide, holds problem and scope, translates strategy</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Timeline management and milestone tracking</li>
                                <li>Scope control and requirement management</li>
                                <li>Risk assessment and mitigation planning</li>
                                <li>Strategy translation into actionable plans</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Present throughout sprint for scope management. Leads planning and estimation activities.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card designer">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Designer/Prototyper</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Play Designer</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Builds prototype efficiently, focuses on user flows and interface clarity</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>UI/UX design and user flow mapping</li>
                                <li>Prototype creation and iteration</li>
                                <li>Usability optimization and design systems</li>
                                <li>Visual design and interaction patterns</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Central to Diverge/Dream and Prototype phases. Provides design input during Understand phase user journey mapping.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card researcher">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Researcher/Customer Expert</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Scout</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Writes test plans, runs interviews, synthesizes insights, understands customers</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>User research and customer insight synthesis</li>
                                <li>Test planning and interview facilitation</li>
                                <li>Usability testing and results analysis</li>
                                <li>Customer journey mapping and persona development</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Critical for Test & Learn phase. Provides customer insights during Understand phase and validates assumptions throughout.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="role-card growth">
                        <div class="role-header">
                            <h4>Growth/Marketing Expert</h4>
                            <span class="sports-analogy">Special Teams Coach</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="role-description">Ensures solution is positioned effectively against competitors</p>
                        <div class="role-details">
                            <h5>Key Responsibilities:</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Market positioning and competitive analysis</li>
                                <li>Growth strategy and user acquisition planning</li>
                                <li>Messaging framework and value proposition</li>
                                <li>Go-to-market strategy development</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h5>When to Engage:</h5>
                            <p>Key contributor during Understand phase for competitive analysis. Essential for Demo Day and launch planning in MVP sprints.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="team-formations">
                    <h4>Example Team Formations</h4>
                    <div class="formation-examples">
                        <div class="formation-card">
                            <h5>Discovery Sprint Formation</h5>
                            <p>Minimum viable team for rapid validation</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Facilitator + Decider + Designer + Researcher + 1 Technical contributor</li>
                                <li><strong>Size:</strong> 5 people</li>
